>An FBI friend of mine who is well aware of these issues suspects that
>it is the Baby Bells who have been responsible for some of the recent
>wiretapping legislation.  As he understands it, whereas now the phone
>companies get no (or little) remuneration for allowing law enforcement
>access for wiretapping, the new bills not only require the technical
>means to access communications, but also require the government to pay
>for those means.
>
>To wit:  Wiretapping, it's not illegal, it's a growth market.



This is truly frightening.


The last time I dealt with the phone company, you had to be talking about
millions of $$ before something was worth thinking about.


How much would each tap cost?


How many taps do you need to have to make significant money on tapping?

